    whyDrHendry: `Dr. William Hendry holds a Doctor of Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine (DAOM) from East West College of Natural Medicine — the highest doctoral credential available in this field. He is NCBAHM board-certified (Dipl. O.M., Cert. #114498) with over 25 years of clinical experience treating thousands of patients across a wide range of conditions. He served on staff at Prisma Health for 9 years with hospital privileges — a distinction extremely rare among acupuncturists — where he co-led a landmark 3-year Emergency Department study on needling techniques as alternatives to opioids for acute pain management. That study has 5 peer-reviewed publications and 52 citations. When you receive acupuncture at IHP, you receive treatment from a clinician whose work has shaped the evidence base for the profession.`,
