      text: `Conventional pain management often relies on NSAIDs, opioids, muscle relaxants, or corticosteroid injections. These can provide short-term relief but carry significant risks — GI bleeding, dependency, adrenal suppression, and joint degradation with repeated injections. Acupuncture offers a different mechanism: it activates the body's endogenous pain-modulating systems (endorphins, serotonin, norepinephrine) and reduces inflammatory mediators without introducing exogenous chemicals. A 2018 meta-analysis in the Journal of Pain including 39 trials and nearly 21,000 patients found acupuncture significantly superior to both sham acupuncture and no-acupuncture controls for chronic pain — with effect sizes comparable to first-line pharmaceutical interventions. Unlike medications, acupuncture outcomes tend to hold after treatment ends, often improving over time with maintenance sessions.`
