    slug: "pregnancy-acupuncture",
    opening: `Each trimester presents a completely different clinical picture, and the treatment has to change with it. First trimester: anti-emetic points, fatigue support, anxiety — nothing that moves downward strongly. Second trimester: sacroiliac dysfunction, round ligament, heartburn, the postural load starting to build. Third trimester: fetal positioning if we need it, birth preparation, sleep that is becoming impossible. I've been treating pregnant patients for over twenty-five years. Every trimester is a different patient, clinically.`,
