    slug: "custom-herbal-formulations",
    opening: `No two patients with the same diagnosis get the same formula. That's the entire point. Two patients with PCOS can have completely different Chinese medical patterns — one is Liver Qi Stagnation with Phlegm-Damp, the other is Kidney Yang Deficiency with Blood Stasis. The base formula for each is different. The modifications within the base are different. The dose is adjusted for body weight, digestive strength, and what else they're taking. I compound from our in-house stock and dispense at the appointment. The formula you receive is written for you specifically, not pulled off a shelf.`,
    howItWorks: `After Chinese medical diagnosis (tongue, pulse, symptom pattern), Dr. Hendry writes a custom prescription specifying each herb, its form (raw, granule, or powder), and the gram quantity per day. The formula is mixed from our herb inventory and dispensed as granule powder to be dissolved in hot water, or as raw herbs for traditional decoction. The prescription is adjusted at each follow-up appointment as your pattern shifts and improves.`,
